-- Canada Will Keep Troops in Afghanistan After 2011 for Training, CTV Says
-- B y   T h e o p h i l o s   A r g i t i s
-- 2010-11-11T04:24:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-11/canada-will-keep-troops-in-afghanistan-after-2011-for-training-ctv-says.html
Canadian Prime Minister  Stephen Harper  said his country plans to maintain troops in Afghanistan
for training after the country’s military mission ends next year,
CTV reported.  Harper, in an  interview  with the Canadian broadcaster, said
the country could have troops in Afghanistan until 2014 in a
non-combat role. Canada currently has about 3,000 soldiers in
Afghanistan, a deployment that’s scheduled to end in July 2011.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Theophilos Argitis  in Ottawa at 
